&gt; Carol,
&gt; Saging is good but if there is any fear or worry or concern about this
&gt; entity, the fear is enough to actually feed the entity strength. When I am
&gt; facing a &quot;hostile&quot; entity I literally step out of my &quot;self&quot; and one of my
&gt; Guides will step in an take command of whatever task we are trying to
&gt; complete.
&gt; The first time this happened was when my girl friend and I were on a date.
&gt; We had gone to play some games at one of Esther&#39;s girlfriends house. The
&gt; girlfriend was &quot;possessed.&quot; The girl friend had a date and suddenly one of
&gt; my Guides mentioned that the young woman was possessed and needed to be
&gt; cleansed. The Guide also mentioned that the young woman&#39;s date was a
&gt; minister-in-training at a small school nearby. But the guy was not yet
&gt; ready to face this type of event.
&gt; I was told to wait until he left and then the both of us could start the
&gt; possession ceremony. Once the guy left, Esther and I approached the young
&gt; woman and explained what we had been shown and asked her if she wished to
&gt; be cleansed. She said yes and asked us to start. It needs to be understood
&gt; that this young woman was in a wheel chair because she had some sort of
&gt; deformity of her legs and they were basically unusable.
&gt; Esther and I started with prayers. We asked to be covered with the white
&gt; light of the Ruach Ha-Kodesh (The Spirit, the Holy). The young woman
&gt; started to curse us in languages that we did not understand, nor cared
&gt; about. Eventually, the young woman levitated out of her wheel chair and
&gt; floated through her parents house. We walked behind her saying prayers.
&gt; Our prayers became so fervent that we understood that we were speaking to
&gt; one another by thought and not orally. Then I felt as if I was moved aside
&gt; in my spirit and a Guide came forward and commanded the spirit to leave.
&gt; The young woman then slowly settled back into her wheel chair, she gave
&gt; one more scream, and then she went limp. She feel into a really deep sleep
&gt; of exhaustion.
&gt; Esther tucked the girl friend into her bed covered her and stayed for the
&gt; rest of the evening. The next morning, they both went to church and the
&gt; young woman sang in her wheel chair as she had never had sung previously.
&gt; Full of joy and happiness.
&gt; Al
